[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    117[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" entry on sanction-list integration: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"The OIG List of Excluded Individuals/Entities (LEIE) is a separate authoritative source of providers excluded from federal healthcare programs ... Cross-checking the matched NPI against the LEIE catches sanctioned providers before they end up in the directory."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m And in Variations and Extensions: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Sanction-list integration (LEIE) as a parallel verification pipeline."[38;2;180;142;173m*[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    118[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe places LEIE cross-checking in the production-gaps and variations sections, framing it as a "you'll want to add this" feature. In the federal-payer compliance regime, LEIE checks are not optional: 42 USC § 1320a-7 prohibits federal healthcare programs from paying for items or services furnished by an excluded individual or entity, and OIG sub-regulatory guidance recommends that providers be screened against the LEIE prior to hire and on a monthly basis thereafter. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m The OIG Special Advisory Bulletin on the Effect of Exclusion from Participation in Federal Health Care Programs is the primary guidance; the chapter editor should verify the current citation. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[38;2;191;97;106m For organizations participating in Medicare Advantage, Medicaid Managed Care, or any federally-funded program, the LEIE check is table stakes. Three concrete consequences:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    119[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    120[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mA matched NPI without a LEIE cross-check exposes the institution to recoupment risk.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A claim paid to an excluded provider is recoupable; CMP penalties under § 1320a-7a may apply. The matcher's output is the substrate the credentialing system, claims pipeline, and directory build on; if the matcher does not surface the exclusion status, downstream systems inherit the gap.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    121[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    122[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe federal-payer compliance program is the same population the No Surprises Act regulates.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly elevates the No Surprises Act to compliance infrastructure framing in the Honest Take; the LEIE check belongs in the same architectural tier, not in variations.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    123[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    124[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe architectural integration is structurally identical to the NPPES drift-detection pattern the recipe already specifies.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Monthly LEIE file ingest to S3, normalize, index, cross-check at attach time and on a monthly batch refresh, emit [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprovider_sanctioned[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m events on EventBridge with immediate consumer fan-out (claims hold, directory removal, credentialing review). The recipe's drift-detection-and-event-emit primitives transfer directly.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    125[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    126[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Promote LEIE integration from variations to the main architecture. Add to the architecture diagram a parallel [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mLEIE Verification[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m flow consuming the monthly OIG LEIE file, with a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mleie-sanction-status[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m table or column on [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprovider-npi-assignment[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m carrying the most recent check timestamp and result. Add to the Step Functions monthly batch-refresh workflow a step that cross-checks every active assignment against the latest LEIE file. Add to the EventBridge fan-out a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprovider_sanctioned[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m detail-type that downstream consumers (claims, credentialing, directory) subscribe to. Update the Honest Take to name LEIE alongside the deactivation flag as the highest-priority drift events. Reference 42 USC § 1320a-7 and the OIG Special Advisory Bulletin as the regulatory anchor.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    127[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
