[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    470[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe propagation latency budget for consent revocation is not specified.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m State and federal regulations may require consent revocations to take effect within a specified window (e.g., 24 hours under some state HIE rules; immediately for some federal categories). The architecture should specify the budget.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    471[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    472[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add to the Why-These-Services / ElastiCache paragraph and to the General Architecture Pattern: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Consent-cache invalidation on revocation is synchronous: the consent-revocation EventBridge event triggers the invalidate-on-event Lambda which (a) deletes the cached consent state, (b) writes a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mconsent_revoked_at[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m flag in the cross-org MPI for the affected patient with the revocation effective time, (c) emits a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcross_facility_match_invalidated[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m event for downstream consumers. In-flight queries that have already read the cache but have not yet released data must re-check consent at the release-and-audit step against the system-of-record (not the cache); the system-of-record check is synchronous with a tight timeout (500ms) and fail-closed on timeout. The propagation latency budget for consent revocation is 60 seconds from registry emit to release-path effect; CloudWatch alarms on propagation latency exceeding 60 seconds at P99 surface drift in the invalidation pipeline. The fail-closed posture on consent extends through the in-flight-query lifecycle, not just the initial cache-or-system-of-record read."[38;2;180;142;173m*[K
