[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    503[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The architecture says ElastiCache holds the blocking-index but does not specify the cluster sizing methodology, the eviction policy, or the warm-up strategy at HIE scale. At fifty participating organizations and three million queries per month, the blocking index can be tens to hundreds of GB depending on the population size and the blocking-key cardinality. Without explicit sizing, the implementation may be undersized and produce cache misses that fall through to DynamoDB at higher cost and latency.[K
