[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # is auditable. Log structural metadata only (encounter_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # language_pair, deployment_posture, segment counts, escalation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # events), never raw audio references that could leak biometric
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # content, never source or target transcript content that could
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # leak PHI, never patient demographics that could enable
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # re-identification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Adaptive retry handles throttling from Transcribe, Translate,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Bedrock, Polly, DynamoDB, S3, EventBridge, CloudWatch, and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Secrets Manager. Real-time medical interpretation has tight
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # per-utterance latency budgets: 1.5 to 3 seconds end-to-end
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # for the conversational flow to stay natural. The retry config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # below favors fewer attempts on the latency-critical path so
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # a stalled vendor does not blow the budget; the audit and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # archival path uses more generous retry tuning.
