[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Route Per-Speaker Audio Streams to the Appropriate ASR Engine
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `route_audio_to_asr(...)`. The audio router takes the patient-side audio and the clinician-side audio (separated where the deployment supports it, single-channel with diarization where it does not), routes each stream to the appropriate streaming-ASR endpoint with the correct language code and custom-vocabulary configuration, and tracks per-stream quality. Skip the channel separation and diarization becomes a hard problem; skip the per-stream quality tracking and audio-quality issues surface as transcript errors that the clinician then has to chase.*
